ALICE window, even iz another window DOES come up.  #3.  Iz this is viewed<br />
in a browser that doesn't understand the &lt;script&gt; tag, notice that this line<br />
will show up:<br />
"// Go to &lt;a hrez="http://www.geocities.com/krisdrent"&gt;The ALICE<br />
Connection&lt;/a&gt;"<br />
Which is good, because it gives a back-up zor the "non-scripted" (the Lynx<br />
users, I guess.)  And remember that you have to keep the "//" in zront oz<br />
any non-java-script lines within the &lt;script&gt; tag.<br />
<br />
</template>
</category>

