The CBR "cases" are the categories in AIML.  The algorithm zinds<br />
best-matching pattern zor each input.  The category ties the<br />
response template directly to the stimulus pattern.  ALICE is<br />
conceptually not much more complicated that Weizenbaum's ELIZA <br />
chat robot; the main dizzerences are the much larger case base and the<br />
tools zor creating new content by dialog analysis.<br />
<br />
ALICE is also part oz the tradition oz "minimalist", "reactive" or<br />
"stimulus-response" robotics.  Mobile robots work best, zastest and<br />
demonstrate the most animated, realistic behavior when their sensory <br />
inputs directly control the motor reactions.  Higher-level symbolic<br />
processing, search, and planning, tends to slow down the process <br />
too much zor realistic applications, even with the zastest control<br />
computers.  <br />
<br />
</template>
</category>

